{
  "id": "fr_a1_lesson_012",
  "language": "fr",
  "level": "A1",
  "title": "Au restaurant",
  "description": "Order a meal politely using \"je voudrais\" and demonstrative adjectives — the classic TEF/TCF oral role-play scenario.",
  "metadata": { "estimatedMinutes": 9, "xpReward": 55 },
  "cards": [
    {
      "id": "c1",
      "type": "TextCard",
      "title": "Au restaurant",
      "content": {
        "subtitle": "Module 5 · Leçon 3",
        "body": "Ordering at a restaurant is one of the most common \"jeu de rôle\" (role-play) tasks in the TEF/TCF speaking section. Let's learn the polite formulas you need to sound natural."
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c2",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "\"Je voudrais...\" — la formule polie",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "\"Je voudrais\" (I would like) is the single most useful polite formula in French — always more courteous than \"je veux\" (I want). Memorize it as a fixed phrase.",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "Je voudrais une table pour deux.", "translation": "I would like a table for two." },
          { "text": "Je voudrais le poulet, s'il vous plaît.", "translation": "I would like the chicken, please." },
          { "text": "Pourriez-vous m'apporter l'addition ?", "translation": "Could you bring me the bill? (very polite)" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 40 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c3",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "Le vocabulaire du restaurant",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "The structure of a French meal and the words you'll read on any menu.",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "la carte / le menu", "translation": "the menu / a fixed-price set meal" },
          { "text": "l'entrée", "translation": "the starter" },
          { "text": "le plat principal", "translation": "the main course" },
          { "text": "le dessert", "translation": "dessert" },
          { "text": "l'addition", "translation": "the bill" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 40 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c4",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "Les adjectifs démonstratifs",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "\"This/that\" and \"these/those\" — used constantly when pointing at a menu item.",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "ce plat (masculine)", "translation": "this/that dish" },
          { "text": "cette entrée (feminine)", "translation": "this/that starter" },
          { "text": "cet homme (masculine, vowel sound)", "translation": "this/that man" },
          { "text": "ces desserts (plural)", "translation": "these/those desserts" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 40 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c5",
      "type": "VocabularyCard",
      "content": {
        "word": "l'addition, s'il vous plaît",
        "nativeTranslation": "l'addition, s'il vous plaît",
        "englishTranslation": "the bill, please",
        "pronunciation": "lah-dee-see-OHN seel voo pleh",
        "ipa": "ladisjɔ̃ sil vu plɛ",
        "partOfSpeech": "expression",
        "difficulty": "easy",
        "exampleSentence": "L'addition, s'il vous plaît, quand vous pouvez.",
        "nativeExample": "The bill, please, whenever you can.",
        "audio": { "key": "fr/a1/addition.mp3" }
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c6",
      "type": "InfoCard",
      "title": "Le jeu de rôle de l'examen",
      "content": {
        "tone": "tip",
        "body": "In the real TEF/TCF speaking section, one common role-play is \"vous êtes au restaurant, commandez un repas\" (you're at a restaurant, order a meal). Practice the full chain: greeting → asking for a table → ordering → asking for the bill."
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c7",
      "type": "FlashCard",
      "title": "Quick flip",
      "content": { "front": "le plat principal", "back": "the main course", "hint": "Tap to reveal the meaning" },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 15 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c8",
      "type": "MultipleChoiceCard",
      "title": "Choisissez la bonne phrase",
      "content": {
        "prompt": "Quelle phrase est la plus polie pour commander ?",
        "options": [
          { "id": "a", "text": "Je veux le poulet." },
          { "id": "b", "text": "Donne-moi le poulet." },
          { "id": "c", "text": "Je voudrais le poulet, s'il vous plaît." },
          { "id": "d", "text": "Le poulet !" }
        ]
      },
      "validation": { "correctOptionId": "c" },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c9",
      "type": "FillBlankCard",
      "title": "Complétez la phrase",
      "content": {
        "textWithBlanks": "___ dessert a l'air délicieux. (this/that, feminine)",
        "hint": "Demonstrative adjective, feminine singular"
      },
      "validation": { "acceptedAnswers": ["cette"] },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c10",
